From 924f4232546df251c645a63928229f2589bfba18 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: rkvenc forward-port <forward-port@local>
Date: Sun, 28 Jun 2026 08:34:01 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] video: rockchip: RK3588 vendor MPP (rkvenc2/rkvdec2) +
 RGA3/RGA2 drivers

Forward-port of the Rockchip 6.1 BSP out-of-tree drivers to v6.18:
 - MPP service framework (rk_vcodec.ko, /dev/mpp_service)
 - VEPU580/rkvenc2 H.264/H.265 hardware encoder
 - rkvdec2 H.264/H.265/VP9 hardware decoder
 - multi_rga RGA3/RGA2 2D accelerator (/dev/rga)

API deltas vs 6.1: class_create() arg, MODULE_IMPORT_NS quoting, dma_buf
*_unlocked variants, hrtimer_setup, follow_pfnmap_start, iommu cookie_type
guard. BSP soc/rockchip services stubbed via compat/ shims. rkvdec2 attach
returns -EPROBE_DEFER (not -ENOMEM/oops) when ccu or core0 not yet probed.
rkvenc2 devfreq-remove underflow guarded. SoC-specific hack/ helpers kept
(they are #included by mpp_rkvdec2*.c; rk3568/px30/rk3576 bodies #ifdef'd out).
